## 5. Explicit "do not touch without flagging first" list

- The verified, working authentication flow (registration, login, JWT
  issuance/validation) — extend it if needed, but do not refactor it
  speculatively.
- The `require_active_counsellor` dependency's existing verification-status
  check — this can be *extended* (e.g. to check `user_roles` instead of the
  single `role` column, once that migration lands) but its underlying safety
  check (a counsellor must be properly verified to act as one) must not be
  removed or weakened.
- The `bcrypt==4.0.1` pin (see Section 2).

